      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The ideal consumer in emerging markets like Dubai, Shanghai, or Lagos would still be predominantly male, but with a more diverse ethnic background, including Middle Eastern, Asian, and African heritage. They would be aged 30-50, with a strong appreciation for luxury but also a desire to showcase their wealth and status through their watch. This consumer would likely be involved in international business, travel frequently, and have a taste for both traditional and modern luxury. They might be less concerned with the subtlety of European aristocracy and more interested in bold, statement pieces that reflect their cosmopolitan lifestyle. While they still value quality and prestige, they may also be more open to innovative designs that incorporate elements from their own cultures, creating a fusion of Western luxury and local flair.",
      "source": "target",
